		consists of (after splitting) and the number of culled gprims
		grids/micropolys.

2001-05-29  tburge
	* render/ri.cpp 1.21:
		Changed Gaussian and Sinc to match what PRMan and 3.2 spec use
		  The Sinc filter is windowed by a raised cosine (von Hann
		Window), this additional math matches the PRMan sinc.

2001-05-29  mbaas
	* render/renderer.cpp 1.23:
	* render/renderer.h 1.11:
	* render/stats.cpp 1.2:
	* render/stats.h 1.5:
		Bug fix: Statistics variables weren't reset at the beginning of a frame.
		Moved the time variable and PrintStats() method from CqRenderer to CqStats.
		Added new timers for shading and individal frame time vs total time.
		Added methods to increase the counters instead of giving out references
		to them.

	* render/imagebuffer.cpp 1.13:
	* render/ri.cpp 1.22:
	* render/shadervariable.cpp 1.4:
	* render/shadervm.cpp 1.6:
		Stats values are increased by a method in CqStats now.
		ri.cpp contains the Start/Stop methods for the various timers.

	* render/micropolygon.cpp 1.6:
		Stats values are increased by a method in CqStats now.
		Bug fix: For motion micropolys the sample hit count was increased twice
		per hit.

2001-05-25  pgregory
	* libdd/dd.cpp 1.3:
		Tidy up the sockets stuff, now cleans up after itself better, 
		and ensures that driver processes left hanging around (i.e.
		framebuffer) don't cause problems on the next run.

2001-05-24  tburge
	* render/attributes.h 1.5:
	* render/ri.cpp 1.20:
		Added attribute storage for two matrices needed to convert
		basis and trying to figure out nicest looking way to add it in.

	* render/ri.cpp 1.19:
		Just adding comments about change of basis.  No code changed.

	* render/cellnoise.cpp 1.3:
		Ooops, forgot to mention that I removed the extra permutation
		for cellnoiseU,V.

	* render/cellnoise.cpp 1.2:
		Adding a test.  If anyone gets a chance let me know if you
		think the distribution of resulting colors is more centered on
		BMRT and maybe PRMan than my cellnoise function.  PRMan and
		RenderDotC give their noise functions a certain statistical
		property, so maybe cellnoise is skewed a bit to the center too.

